      <h1 class="headline">China's government expands its overseas financial investments fast, bold and unnoticed.</h1>
      <h2 class="subhead">This projects presents a detailed chronogical and geographic breakdown of these investments.</h2>
      <p class="byline">By Frida Cai</p>
      <p class="date">Published August 8 2019</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story-body">
       <p class="body-text">China occupys news headlines today. However, it is still beyond the common knowledge about the scale of China's official financial deployement in foreign countries. This projects presents a detailed breakdown of these projects chronogically and geographiclaly.</p>
      <p class="body-text">Since China's government does not participate in any public recording of its global financial activities, researchers and journalists could only rely on China's self-report. So far, the dataset published by AidData in 2018 is the most comprehensive source of Chinese official projects overseas.</p>
      <p class="body-text">The investments are categorized under Official Development Assistance (ODA, also known as Aid), Other Official Flows (OOF primarily for commercial or representative intentions) and Vague Official Finance.</p>

    <div class="chart-section">
